<br>
I haven't read this books yet, but I'm going to B&amp;N this friday and I considering buying it. I'd love to read it and then its sequel! I always see it and read the back, but I just haven't read it! I don't know why! <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:verdana;font-size:x-small;">Luv</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:white;font-family:verdana;font-size:x-small;">ya!</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.fortunecity.com/victorian/stone/27/names/d/danielle01.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bchristlikebooklovers.showUserPublicProfile?gid=femalenomad>FemaleNomad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezHopeful</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#3333ff>(4/28/03 10:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fchristlikebookloversfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ...</span><hr size=1> No, they're not Christian - and I don't know how the titles can sound bad, since there are only two books, and they're called &quot;The Sisterhood of the Traveling Pants&quot; and &quot;The Second Summer of the Sisterhood.&quot;<br>
<br>
But anyway. The first one is in paperback now. Really, if you are between 14 and 30, you'd probably LOVE these books. I bought the first one in hardcover ('cause it was only $3 at work), and I'm almost done with the second one. I might buy it, too.<br>
<br>
The girls deal with real issues, and life isn't perfect for them. I really think the author is amazing - she writes four characters, and each one has a very particular personality of her own. I think there's something for every girl to relate to in these stories. I really can't say enough good about them. Honestly.<br>
<br>
They are not for &quot;immature&quot; readers, though. Not that they're filled with sex or anything - far from it. But the books do wander through the whole experience of being a teenage girl, so...<br>
<br>
Anyway. Read them! Definitely start with the first one, since it's in paper now. Finally. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:FF9900;font-family:Gigi;font-size:medium;">Amy</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->I always prefer to believe the best of everybody - it saves so much trouble</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bchristlikebooklovers.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lilamazing>LilAmazing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezHappy</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#3333ff>(5/1/03 4:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fchristlikebookloversfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ...</span><hr size=1> For those of you that read both 1 and 2, which was your fav?  I liked the second book better because I thought the situations were more interesting.  My fav character is Carmen because I can relate to her the most.  I think that the best thing about these books is the friendship the four girls have.  It always makes me wish I had friends like that.  Oh well. lol <p><br>
